In the presence of active and alive bacteria, the activity of dehydrogenase enzyme caused reduction of Resazurin and its conversion to Resorufin, whereby the color of the solution changed from blue to pink. Inactive bacteria do not develop any changes in Resazurin and its color remains blue (Liu 2006; Tizzard et al. 2006; Zare et al. 2015). The percentage of reduction in the growth was obtained using Eq. 2.2Diminished activity of dehydrogenase enzyme in Resazurin conversion%=A-BA×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
