Firstly, one loop of P. aeruginosa was added to 25 mL of broth culture medium to prepare bacterial suspension. The turbidity developed in the suspension had a density of about 3 × 108 cells/mL. Thereafter, dilution was performed until its optical density was equal to a solution 1 McFarland by this culture medium. After that, its turbidity was measured by a spectrophotometer device at wavelength of 625 nm (Toolabi et al. 2011). In the next stage, 100 µL of bacteria containing suspension was inoculated on a plate containing the culture medium and acetamiprid toxin at different concentrations. Finally, using Eq. 3, the growth inhibition percentage was determined.3%Growth inhibition=A-BA×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
